text: Raimundo José do Rego Sarmento (born 10 October 1994) also known as Jeca is a football player who currently plays for Timor-Leste national football team. ==International career== Jeca made his senior international debut against Mongolia national football team in the 2018 FIFA World Cup qualification (AFC) on 12 March 2015 as a substitute in the 89th minute to replace Diogo Santos.Timor-Leste vs Mongolia Match Report ==References== ==External links== * Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:East Timorese footballers Category:Timor-Leste international footballers Category:Association football defenders
